### 5. No Global Error Handler (OWASP A09:2021 – Security Logging & Monitoring Failures)

If any route throws an unhandled error, Express's default handler sends a **full stack trace** in development mode, leaking internal paths, library versions, and architecture details.

**Recommendation:** Add an error-handling middleware at the end of the middleware chain:

```js
// Must be defined AFTER all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(`[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${err.stack}`);
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
  // Never send err.message or err.stack to the client
});
